  "prompt": "How can I know who views my Instagram profile?",
  "response": "Instagram does not provide a feature that allows you to see exactly who views your profile. This is a deliberate design choice to protect user privacy.\n\nHere's a breakdown of what you *can* see and how it might give you some insights:\n\n*   **Profile Visits from Insights (Business/Creator Accounts):** If you have an Instagram business or creator account, you can access Insights. This data gives you an *aggregate* number of profile visits within a certain time frame (e.g., the last 7 or 30 days). However, it *does not* tell you *who* those visitors are. You'll see a total number, but no specific usernames.\n*   **Story Viewers:**  When you post a story, you *can* see a list of who viewed it. This is the *only* place Instagram directly shows you who's looking at your content. However, this only applies to stories that are still live (within 24 hours) or archived stories you specifically check.\n*   **Reel Viewers:** Similar to stories, you can see how many people viewed your reel and a list of the users that viewed it.\n*   **Likes and Comments:** If someone likes or comments on your posts or reels, you know they've seen that specific piece of content.\n*   **Follower Requests:**  If someone sends you a follow request, you know they've visited your profile.\n*   **Third-Party Apps:** **Avoid these.** There are many third-party apps claiming to show you who views your profile. These apps are almost always scams, violate Instagram's terms of service, and can compromise your account security (e.g., steal your password, install malware). Instagram actively discourages and often blocks these apps. They are *never* reliable.\n\n**In summary:**\n\n*   **No direct way to see who views your Instagram profile.**\n*   Insights provide aggregate data, not individual user data.\n*   Story/Reel viewers are visible for the duration of the story or reel and after if the story is archived.\n*   Be wary of third-party apps promising this feature\u2014they are likely scams.\n\n**Focus on creating engaging content:** Instead of worrying about who is viewing your profile, focus on creating high-quality content that resonates with your target audience. This will naturally increase engagement and help you reach a wider audience.\n",
